&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE OPPORTUNITY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MISUMI Americas is the product of two strong brands coming together with a shared ambition: to become the defining force in digital manufacturing. MISUMI USA brings decades of established trust, global scale, and an unmatched catalog. Fictiv brings a track record of technology-led innovation and a relentless drive to reimagine how manufacturing gets done. Together, we&#39;re not just combining companies — we&#39;re building something more capable than either could be alone, with the resources of an industry leader and the energy of a company that still thinks like a challenger.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IT infrastructure is foundational to getting that right. We&#39;ve combined two organizations onto a shared technology platform, and we&#39;re doing it deliberately — investing in world-class security, modern tooling, and a team that treats every employee as a high-value customer. This is your chance to own that effort end to end: finish the integration, then run and grow the IT organization that will support MISUMI Americas for years to come.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a steady-state role. It&#39;s a rare window where someone with real technical depth — hands-on with Entra ID, Intune, SIEM, Slack Enterprise Grid — can shape the architecture of a combined organization and leave a durable mark. You&#39;ll lead a globally distributed team of ~14 across India, China, Mexico, and the US, and you&#39;ll work directly in the systems you oversee, not just manage the people who do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL OWN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IT operations &amp;amp; service delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep business-critical systems available, performant, and well-supported across the combined organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a unified, responsive IT support experience regardless of which legacy company an employee came from&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set and maintain clear SLAs; define severity levels, escalation paths, and incident communication protocols&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor system health proactively and resolve infrastructure issues before they become outages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integration (time-bound, ~8–12 months remaining)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the remaining consolidation work: identity migration onto Entra ID, Google Workspace → Microsoft 365, Okta decommission, CrowdStrike Falcon fleet-wide deployment, next-gen SIEM integration, and domain rebrand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the timeline, quality, and business continuity throughout — this is yours to close out&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
